Text.Text: Why, 'ello there, love; m'name's Gohar - welcome to the Salty Dog.  What'll it be for yeh?
Ye'd best watch yer tongue, *love*... if yeh don't care for me or me lip, then get yer hide outta me tavern.
Come now, love... one doesn't come inta my tavern asking questions.  A dangerous thing t'do, it is - unless yer fishing for daggers in yer back rather than answers.
Eh?  Well... when I was a 'ired blade some twelve years past, I won it in a knife fight.  I'd planned on sellin' the place an' usin' the coin fer ale an' whores in Luskan, right?
Welcome to th'Salty Dog, traveler.  M'name's Gohar... what'll it be for yeh?
Word to th'wise, friend... one doesn't come my tavern asking questions.  A dangerous thing t'do, it is - unless yer fishing for daggers in yer back rather than answers.
Ah, now, welcome back, love.  What'll it be for yeh?
Welcome back.  What'll it be for yeh this time?
Well, now, if it innit the lass with the witch's tongue!  What'll it be, love?
Are yeh *mad?!*  I sure as all the 'ells not be servin' drinks while the town's in danger o' being drowned in goblin arrows - off to the Palisade with yeh!

Eh, I was hopin' ye might be by... I just wanted t'say... er, that is... I 'eard what ye did, and yer probably the reason th' docks and th' Salty Dog's not in flames right now.  Thanks for pitchin' in for the town's sake.
...but I fell 'ard for the former owner's widow an' decided to plant meself.  The good woman passed last winter, though, so the tavern's me missus now...
Oh, aye, *goblins* - that would explain the warning horn from the Palisade and the cries of "to arms!  To arms!"  Seems to me ye've already 'ad one t'many tankards, friend.  Off with ye!
I'm *not* going t'warn ye AGAIN.  Off with ye!
They're in the corner, splitting kegs 'tween them.  If I were ye, I'd forget what business I 'ad with them - they don't take kindly t'being interrupted.
They're in the corner, splitting kegs 'tween them.  If I were ye, I'd forget what business I 'ad with them - they don't take kindly t'being interrupted.
Oh, ol' Cahl-Hyred said that, did 'e?  Aye, I remember Donovan - 'e died years ago, lost on Maer Dualdon, so ye'll have no luck finding 'im now.
Found 'is skiff washed up onna shore is 'ow I know.  Found it a few winters ago - poor Donovan, good fellow, but couldn't 'old his ale, and 'e wasn't too sharp, neither.
Well, aye, I 'ave it laying around 'ere - about as pickled as Donovan hisself.  If ye want it, it's yours.  It's the least I can do after ye drove those ratty goblin bastards off the Docks.
Here ye are.  "Viera's Gaze," right there on the prow.  Name o' his poor wife, I think.  Heard she passed away from grief, so the tale goes.
Aye, well, if it innit th' one who put Black Geoffrey in an early grave.  Looks to me like ye'd best settle 'is bill, love.
Aye, well, if it innit th' one who put Black Geoffrey in an early grave.  Looks to me like ye'd best settle 'is bill, friend.
Thirty coin, last count - between 'im an' 'is drunk friends.  Let's 'ave it, now.
Right enough then, a pleasure doin' business.  What'll it be for yeh?
Right enough, then.  What'll it be for yeh, love?
As soon as yeh drew blood in the Salty Dog, ye owe me 'is gold, an' count yerself lucky I only ask ye to pay 'is bill, ye hound's get.  Ye owes me thirty gold, so 'and it over!
I... I'll let it go *this* time, but I'm watching yeh, I am.
Did you know goblins are attacking the town?
There's a goblin attack taking place - grab your weapons, we need all the help we can get.
I was told to come here and find the Iron Collar Mercenary band - do you know where I can find them?
Nothing for now.  Farewell.
Some respect, to start with.  I'll have no more of this "love" nonsense.
Do you know anything about a fisherman named Donovan?  Cahl-Hyred told me he used to drink here.
I was hoping I might ask you some questions.
